<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Streisand Says No More Concerts  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Barbra Streisand says her record-breaking New Year's Eve
concert in Las Vegas was the last of her career.
</P>
<P>
	   "This is the last time I'm going to do any kind of concert," Streisand told
TV Guide following the show. "I don't like performing. I feel like I'm in a
beauty pageant, like I'm 18 and strutting around on stage."
</P>
<P>
	   Fans paid a total $14,694,750 to hear Streisand ring in the new year, an
all-time single concert box-office record, according to the host, MGM Grand
hotel-casino.
</P>
<P>
	   The actress, singer and producer said over the years the media and celebrity
rumors have added to her frustrations about taking the stage.
</P>
<P>
	   "They're making me into a diva, and I'm like this normal person. I do my own
makeup. My hairdresser's been with me for 20 years. I don't know why it is that
we need to denigrate, to knock down. It's so sick," she said in the Jan. 22
issue.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
