Williams added 20 points and 10 assists for the Kings, who won their fifth
straight game and nine in their last 11. Cleveland's Shawn Kemp had 20 points
and nine rebounds, but fouled out with 3:12 to play. Lamond Murray scored 18
points and Mark Bryant had 18 points and 11 rebounds.
</P>
