<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Red Wings 3, Oilers 3, Tie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Steve Yzerman scored a goal and was denied another
on a last-second breakaway Sunday night as the Detroit Red Wings and Edmonton
Oilers skated to a 3-3 tie.
</P>
<P>
	   Yzerman, whose 613th goal tied Mario Lemieux for seventh place on the NHL's
career list, was stopped by Tommy Salo on a short-handed breakaway as overtime
expired.
</P>
<P>
	   Mathieu Dandenault and Vyacheslav Kozlov also scored for Detroit, which
moved into a tie with St. Louis for first place in the Central Division.
</P>
<P>
	   Ethan Moreau had two goals and Jim Dowd had one for the Oilers, who played
to their 12th tie.
</P>
<P>
	   Both teams are winless in three games (0-2-1).
</P>
<P>
	   Scotty Bowman coached his 500th game for the Red Wings and has compiled a
289-147-64 with Detroit.
</P>
<P>
	   Dowd knocked in a rebound from beside the net on a power play at 9:48 of the
third period to tie the game 3-3.
</P>
<P>
	   Kozlov gave Detroit a 3-2 advantage, making a perfect deflection from the
slot on Nicklas Lidstrom's shot on a power play at 9:02 of the second.
</P>
<P>
	   Yzerman's power-play goal at 8:46 of the first put Detroit in front 1-0.
Yzerman, who has 42 goals and 74 points in 50 games against the Oilers, scored
on a rebound of Steve Duchesne's point shot.
</P>
<P>
	   Dandenault made it 2-0 less than three minutes later. His slap shot from the
point beat Salo at 11:30.
</P>
<P>
	   Mike Grier's shot from the right boards deflected off Moreau and past Chris
Osgood at 15:33 of the first to make it 2-1.
</P>
<P>
	   Moreau tied it by knocking in a rebound of Christian Laflamme's point shot
at 8:02 of the second.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
