<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-17 12:52 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Superfund tainted site up for sale  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   STRATFORD, Conn. (AP)- A chunk of land contaminated for decades by the
manufacture of brake linings and auto parts has been cleaned up and is up for
sale.
<P>
	   After years spent cleaning up contamination, legal wrangling and government
negotiations, the Raymark property is going to be auctioned Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   The 33-acre piece of property, where for 70 years Raymark created millions
of cubic yards of contaminated sludge before its plant closed in 1989, was
cleaned up through the federal Superfund program.
</P>
<P>
	   The factory buildings were torn down and a protective, multi-layered cap was
built over the soil contaminated with lead, dioxin, PCBs and asbestos.
</P>
<P>
	   A foundation for a shopping center was built into the cap, which was
completed in 1997, so it would not have to be disturbed during construction.
</P>
<P>
	   The sale of the property is set for Wednesday, when the U.S. Bankruptcy
Court in Bridgeport will hold an auction in open session.
</P>
<P>
	   Several potential bidders are interested in the land and the site is
expected to sell for a minimum of $15 million.
</P>
<P>
	   Reed Rubenstein, a lawyer for the Raymark bankruptcy trustee, said
redeveloping the highly polluted property is like spinning "straw into gold."
</P>
<P>
	   "Really, what we're doing here is something very special," Rubenstein said.
</P>
<P>
	   Though it was physically ready for redevelopment, the property and its
bankrupt owner got caught up in long negotiations with federal agencies over the
sale.
</P>
<P>
	   Finally, in late 1998, a U.S. District Court judge in Hartford ordered the
sale and in Nov. 1999 Judge Alan Shiff of U.S. Bankruptcy Court approved the
sale.
</P>
<P>
	   Stratford officials are pleased at the interest in the property and have
been anxious to get it back on the tax rolls.
</P>
<P>
	   "We're excited that it's going forward," said Richard Buturla, the assistant
town attorney who has been working on the sale.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-01-17-00 1252 </TRAILER>
