<HEADLINE> Kole Named AP Hartford Bureau Chief  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- William J. Kole, chief of bureau for The Associated Press
in Amsterdam for the past three years and a New England native, has been named
bureau chief in Hartford, Conn.
</P>
<P>
	   The appointment was announced Monday by AP President and CEO Louis D.
Boccardi. Kole succeeds Keith Robinson, who was named bureau chief in
Indianapolis.
</P>
<P>
	   Kole, 39, began his AP career in 1988 in Detroit and moved to Lansing as a
Michigan statehouse reporter in 1992. The following year, he transferred to the
International Desk in New York, and two years later he began his foreign service
career in Paris. Kole has been bureau chief in the Netherlands since 1997.
</P>
<P>
	   Kole, who grew up in Massachusetts, studied journalism at Boston University
and worked for The Sun Chronicle in Attleboro, Mass., before joining the AP.
</P>
