February to promote business with the communist country, group
officials said today. Chung hopes to meet leader Kim Jong Il and
discuss several investment projects, including a major industrial
complex on North Korea's west coast, said Kim Yun-kyu, a senior
Hyundai official. Hyundai plans to relocate hundreds of footwear
and other small-scale, labor-intensive South Korean plants to the
industrial complex. Hyundai also is pushing to invest in about a
dozen handicraft and other small businesses in Chung's hometown of
Tongchun on North Korea's east coast.
</P>
