<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Crowd's behavior at St. Bonaventure condemned  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   OLEAN, N.Y (AP) - St. Bonaventure fans who got their team a technical
foul for throwing objects from the stands Saturday got a warning Monday from
Atlantic 10 commissioner Linda Bruno.
<P>
	   "A recurrence of this problem will result in action by the Conference
office," she said.
</P>
<P>
	   Fans threw objects at Temple head coach John Chaney and several Temple
basketball players during the Bonnie's shocking 57-56 win with a 3-point shot at
the buzzer. Chaney himself got a technical foul for smashing a cookie to the
floor to get officials' attention.
</P>
<P>
	   He said the cookie had been thrown at him.
</P>
<P>
	   "The conduct of a few members of that crowd ... provided an atmosphere that
was detrimental to the playing of the game and could have resulted in injury to
our student-athletes, coaches and fans," Ms. Bruno said.
</P>
<P>
	   St. Bonaventure's director of athletics, Gothard Lane, said he has taken
measures to provide a safer environment at the Bonnies' next home game Jan. 29.
</P>
<P>
	   There was also good news for the Bonnies Monday. They earned 49 points in
the Associated Press' Top 25 poll. They placed 30th in the ranking. The team has
not earned a spot in the poll since 1971.
</P>
</TEXT>
