<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   MURRAY HILL, N.J. (AP) - A Lucent Technologies division has been awarded
a $100 million contract by Tyco Submarine Systems Ltd. to provide high-powered
laser modules for use in Tyco's undersea fiber optic networks, the companies
announced Monday.
<P>
	   The modules, which will be supplied by Lucent's Microelectronics Group based
in Allentown, Pa., will double the power of Tyco's existing undersea
telecommunications systems.
</P>
<P>
	   Tyco, a subsidiary of Tyco International Ltd., based in Clark, is a leading
supplier for telecommunications firms building global undersea fiber optic
networks.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   MOUNT OLIVE, N.J. (AP) - Chemical manufacturer BASF Corp. said Monday it has
agreed to purchase the polyurethane systems business of Elkton, Md.-based IPI
International for an undisclosed amount.
</P>
<P>
	   BASF said the acquisition will enable the company to increase its
participation in the spray foam market. The deal is expected to close in the
first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
	   IPI, a subsidiary of PMC Inc., is a global supplier of blended polyurethane
products used primarily in insulation.
</P>
<P>
	   BASF makes plastics, nylon fibers, colorants and automotive coatings. It is
the North American affiliate of BASF Group, which is based in Ludwigshafen,
Germany.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   ATLANTIC CITY, N.J. (AP) - A new $14 million health center, jointly funded
by Atlantic City Medical Center and the Casino Reinvestment Development
Authority, will open Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   AtlantiCare HealthPlex is a 46,650-square-foot facility with an adjoining
child care center. It will offer primary health care as well as services in
obstetrics and gynecology, radiology, occupational medicine, physical therapy
and rehabilitation, laboratory testing and general surgery.
</P>
<P>
	   AtlantiCare, a health care system based in Egg Harbor Township, is the
parent company of Atlantic City Medical Center and five other health care
facilities in southern New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   EATONTOWN, N.J. (AP) - Tachion Networks said Monday it has been awarded a
contract worth up to $35 million by TelePacific Communications to provide the
infrastructure for bundled voice and data services.
</P>
<P>
	   TelePacific, based in Los Angeles, will use Tachion's Fusion 5000 switches
to build networks for corporate customers.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
<P>
	   MURRAY HILL, N.J. (AP) - William Brinkman has been named vice president of
research for Bell Labs, the research and development arm of Lucent Technologies,
effective immediately, the company announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
	   Brinkman succeeds Arun Netravali, who became president of Bell Labs last
October.
</P>
<P>
	   In his new role, Brinkman will oversee 1,200 researchers in mathematics,
communications science, physics and engineering. He previously served as
physical sciences research vice president for the company.
</P>
<P>
	   The Basking Ridge resident holds a graduate degree in physics from the
University of Missouri and spent a year as a postdoctoral fellow at Oxford
University in England.
</P>
<P>
	   Bell Labs has a budget of more than $4 billion and employs 30,000 people in
25 countries.
</P>
<P>
	   ----
</P>
