<HEADLINE> Emergency Landing for Mo. Plane  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- A chartered plane carrying the University of
Missouri basketball team made an emergency landing Monday night because of fears
the plane was losing pressurization.
</P>
<P>
	   The DC-9 charter with 34 people on board, including the crew and the
Missouri traveling party, landed safely at the Springfield airport after
passengers heard a "swishing" noise, said Gary Cyr, Springfield's assistant
director of aviation.
</P>
<P>
	   Emergency vehicles were sent to the runway after the tower was notified of a
possible problem at 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
	   It was determined that a seal had broken on a window. The seal was fixed,
and the plane continued on to Dallas.
</P>
<P>
	   The Tigers play Baylor in Waco, Texas, on Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
