<HEADLINE> Mississippi St. 86, S. Carolina 73  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    STARKVILLE, Miss. (AP) -- Freshman LaToya Thomas scored 23 points and
Jennifer Fambrough and Cynthia Hall each added 14 as No. 22 Mississippi State
beat South Carolina 86-73 on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
	   The Bulldogs (13-2, 2-2 Southeastern Conference) extended their
school-record home winning streak to 15 games, and coach Sharon Fanning improved
to 10-0 lifetime against South Carolina.
</P>
<P>
	   Shaunzinski Gortman led South Carolina (10-6, 3-3) with 22 points, and
Jocelyn Penn added 12 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Mississippi State led 41-31 after a sloppy first half that saw the teams
combine for 31 fouls and 30 turnovers.
</P>
</TEXT>
